      • apply

        public <M> Entity<M,ShardingEnvelope<M>> apply(EntityTypeKey<M> typeKey,
                                               scala.Function1<EntityContext,Behavior<M>> createBehavior)
        Defines how the entity should be created. Used in ClusterSharding.init(akka.cluster.sharding.typed.scaladsl.Entity<M, E>). More optional settings can be defined using the with methods of the returned Entity.

        Any Behavior can be used as a sharded entity actor, but the combination of sharding and persistent actors is very common and therefore PersistentEntity is provided as a convenience for creating such PersistentBehavior.

        Parameters:
        typeKey - A key that uniquely identifies the type of entity in this cluster
        createBehavior - Create the behavior for an entity given a EntityContext (includes entityId)
        Returns:
        (undocumented)
